#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: title
#: content/about/tour414.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Xfce 4.14 tour"
msgstr "Paseo de Xfce 4.14"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "This tour will introduce you to new major features of Xfce 4.14. It only covers improvements made on the surface; for the full list of changes, see the [changelogs](/download/changelogs/).\n"
msgstr "Este recorrido le presentará las nuevas características principales de Xfce 4.14. Solo cubre las mejoras realizadas superficialmente; para obtener la lista completa de cambios, consulte los [registros de cambios](/download/changelogs/).\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Color Profiles Dialog"
msgstr "Cuadro de Diálogo de Perfiles de color"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "A new dialog for setting [color profiles](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/4.14/color) for monitors, printers and scanners was introduced. It acts as a frontend to various daemons that talk directly to colord, e.g. saned (scanners), cupsd (printers) or xiccd (monitors).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The new color profiles dialog][img-color-profiles]\n"
msgstr "![El cuadro de diálogo de nuevos perfiles de color][img-color-profiles]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Several improvements were made to the [display dialog](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/4.14/display). Apart from tweaks to the user interface to make the interaction more intuitive (introducing display numbering, showing a primary indicator with quick access to panel, notification and desktop settings etc.) a feature to save and restore complete display profiles was added. If a single profile exists for a setup, the Xfce settings daemon will automatically enable it. If multiple profiles exist, it will pop up the minimal dialog and offer all profiles in addition to the previously available pre-sets (internal only, mirror, extend and external only).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The primary indicator][img-display-general]\n"
msgstr "![El indicador principal][img-display-general]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The display profile list][img-display-advanced]\n"
msgstr "![La lista de perfiles de visualización][img-display-advanced]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The improved minimal dialog - in this case only showing one profile only which never happens anymore now ;)][img-display-minimal]\n"
msgstr "![El cuadro de diálogo mínimo mejorado: en este caso, solo muestra un perfil, lo que ya no sucede ahora ;)][img-display-minimal]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "Accessibility"
msgstr "Accesibilidad"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "One [accessibility](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-settings/4.14/accessibility) feature that people coming from other desktop environments or operating systems were still missing is to set a (custom) keyboard shortcut (by default: Super+F1) to visually locate the mouse pointer. This feature was added in Xfce 4.14.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The mouse pointer location animation][img-locate-mouse]\n"
msgstr "![La animación de ubicación del puntero del mouse][img-locate-mouse]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "General: Icon size"
msgstr "General: Tamaño del icono"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "A new feature that we introduced in the [panel](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-panel/4.14/start) is being able to control the icon size of all plugins. ('All' may not be technically correct, as not all plugins support the new API as of now, but now they *can*. Plus the Window buttons plugin is an exception, because libwnck doesn't allow anything other than 16px or 32px.) This means setups that were previously impossible, because icons would upscale automatically according to size-steps hard-coded in the panel, are now possible (see below).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "![A 32px tall panel with 16px icons][img-panel-iconsize]\n"
msgstr "![Un panel de 32 píxeles de alto con iconos de 16 píxeles][img-panel-iconsize]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Window buttons: Grouping"
msgstr "Botones de ventana: Agrupados"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "Grouping was improved in the [Window buttons plugin](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-panel/4.14/tasklist), both functionally (by improving the matching and icon-finding) and visually by providing a new group indicator that is less likely to clash with window titles containing an enumeration in brackets.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The new group indicator (two terminal windows)][img-panel-group]\n"
msgstr "![El nuevo indicador de grupo (dos ventanas de terminal)][img-panel-group]\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour414.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Session *(xfce4-session)*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:49 content/about/tour412.md:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "Settings Dialog"
msgstr "Diálogo de configuración"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "As soon as a [session](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-session/4.14/preferences) has been saved a new tab is dynamically added to the settings dialog displaying all saved sessions and allowing to delete one or all of them. This should make it way more discoverable for users if they actually have saved sessions that influence the startup behavior - previously this had to be checked manually in the filesystem.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The settings dialog after saving a session][img-session-saved]\n"
msgstr "![Cuadro de diálogo de configuración después de guardar una sesión][img-session-saved]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pathbar"
msgstr "Barra de ruta"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "Up to Xfce 4.12 [Thunar](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/thunar/4.14/start) offered two options for the pathbar/locationbar. The best of both worlds has now been mixed into one powerful pathbar, featuring both clickable breadcrumbs (i.e. folders), an easily accessible way to hand-type a path as well as an improved look.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Thunar's new pathbar][img-thunar-pathbar]\n"
msgstr "![Nueva barra de ruta de Thunar][img-thunar-pathbar]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Folder Thumbnailer"
msgstr "Miniatura de carpeta"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "Same as on the Desktop you can now save an image with the name 'folder.jpg' in a folder and get it displayed as its icon in the File Manager. Note: [Please read the docs](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/tumbler/available_plugins#customized_thumbnailer_for_folders) on how to set this up (if your distribution hasn't enabled it by default).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Thunar's new folder thumbnails][img-thunar-folder-jpg]\n"
msgstr "![Miniaturas de la nueva carpeta de Thunar][img-thunar-folder-jpg]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:71 content/about/tour414.md:85
#: content/about/tour412.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Panel Plugin"
msgstr "Complemento del panel"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [Power Manager's panel plugin](https://docs.xfce.org/xfce/xfce4-power-manager/4.14/panel-plugin) supports symbolic icons now and uses the standard UPower icon names (making it more compatible with all icon themes). It also shows an indicator if applications inhibit power management functions like suspend (when power is low) or display dimming (after a defined timeout).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Parole's video playback is inhibiting power management][img-xfpm-inhibitors]\n"
msgstr "![El reproductor de vídeo Parole inhibe la administración de energía][img-xfpm-inhibitors]\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour414.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "Notification Service *(xfce4-notifyd)*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour414.md:79 content/about/tour44.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Configuración"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Several new features have been added in Xfce's [Notification service](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/notifyd/start), including a notifications log, the possibility to disable notifications per application, a global 'Do Not Disturb' mode, which inhibits all notifications, and finally a new animation ('slide out').\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The new notification animation 'slide out'][img-notifyd-slideout]\n"
msgstr "![La nueva animación de notificación se 'desliza hacia afuera'][img-notifyd-slideout]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "Furthermore a new panel plugin was added which provides quick access to both the 'Do Not Disturb' mode as well as the log of recent notifications.\n"
msgstr "Además, se agregó un nuevo complemento de panel que brinda acceso rápido tanto al modo 'No molestar' como al registro de notificaciones recientes.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The new panel plugin][img-notifyd-panel]\n"
msgstr "![El complemento nuevo del panel][img-notifyd-panel]\n"

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:91 content/about/tour412.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "Media Player *(parole)*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mini Mode"
msgstr "Modo Mini"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "[Parole](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/parole/start) now features a 'Mini Mode', where the interface is simplified to just display the album artwork and can be positioned over other windows without getting in the way.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Just right-click anywhere in the player window to select 'Mini Mode'...][img-parole-normal-mode]\n"
msgstr "![Simplemente haga clic con el botón derecho en cualquier lugar de la ventana del reproductor para seleccionar 'Modo Mini' ...][img-parole-normal-mode]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Afterwards, enjoy a truly minimalistic playback experience!][img-parole-mini-mode]\n"
msgstr "![Después, ¡Disfruta de una experiencia de reproducción verdaderamente minimalista!][img-parole-mini-mode]\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour414.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "Screensaver *(xfce4-screensaver)*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: content/about/tour414.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "A Modern Locking Experience"
msgstr "Una experiencia de bloqueo moderna"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "The new Xfce [Screensaver](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/screensaver/start) provides a configurable lockscreen experience. You can selectively toggle the lock screen and screensaver, and all Xscreensaver themes are supported (with configuration options) out of the box. If you prefer a blank screen, Xfce Screensaver also includes a blank screen option with DPMS integration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "![The new lock screen, sharing styles with LightDM GTK+ Greeter for a consistent experience.][img-saver-dialog]\n"
msgstr "![La nueva pantalla de bloqueo, comparte estilos con LightDM GTK+ Greeter para una experiencia consistente.][img-saver-dialog]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:110
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Make it your own. Xfce Screensaver supports a multitude of configuration options.][img-saver-preferences]\n"
msgstr "![Hazlo tuyo. El salvapantallas de Xfce admite una multitud de opciones de configuración.][img-saver-preferences]\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour414.md:111
#, no-wrap
msgid "Terminal *(xfce4-terminal)*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:114
#, no-wrap
msgid "Lots and lots of features have accumulated in the [Terminal](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/terminal/start) over the last years. Amongst them 'Undo Close Tab' and 'Close Other Tabs' functionality (similar to web browsers), 'Copy Input to All Tabs', 'Set Title Color' (allows to customize tab text color), 'Save Contents' (saves tab contents to a file), an 'Unsafe Paste' dialog (which prevents the terminal from auto-executing pasted text as a command) and support for zooming. Finally when closing a tab or window, there is a new check for running processes which prevents accidentally closing a terminal that is running a process.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "![Zooming, 'Save Contents' and much more!][img-terminal]\n"
msgstr "![¡Zoom, 'Guardar contenido' y mucho más!][img-terminal]\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/about/tour414.md:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Screenshooter *(xfce4-screenshooter)*"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Xfce [Screenshooter](https://docs.xfce.org/apps/screenshooter/start) gained several notable features, amongst others seeing the size of the screenshot while dragging, moving the selection with the mouse and better [imgur](https://imgur.com) integration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/about/tour414.md:122
#, no-wrap
msgid "![I can drag and move the screenshot area, whoop whoop!][img-screenshooter]\n"
msgstr "![Puede arrastrar y mover el área de captura de pantalla, ¡whoop whoop!][img-screenshooter]\n"

